.Dd April 23, 2026
.Dt MAT_VERBMESSAGE 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm Mat_VerbMessage
.Nd Logs a message if the requested verbose level is enabled.
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include <matio.h>
.Ft int
.Fo Mat_VerbMessage
.Fa "int level"
.Fa "const char *format"
.Fa "..."
.Fc
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn Mat_VerbMessage
function emits a message only when
.Fa level
is less than or equal to the current verbose level set with
.Fn Mat_SetVerbose .
If the library is in silent mode, no message is emitted.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
The function returns 0.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr Mat_SetVerbose 3 ,
.Xr Mat_Message 3